always_included_messages.content:
Based on the user's query, make the best travel plan for the user and save it. Do not ask follow-up questions.
Use your best judgement in finding alternatives if possible. Don't give up - ALWAYS save a plan with the `submit_day_plan` function for each day of the trip!

functions.name: accommodation_search
functions.desc:
Discover accommodations in your desired city.
Example: accommodation_search("Rome") would present a list of hotel rooms in Rome.

city.description: The name of the city where you're seeking accommodation.

functions.name: attraction_search
functions.desc:
Find attractions in a city of your choice.
Example: attraction_search("London") would return attractions in London.

city.description: The name of the city where you're seeking attractions.

functions.name: city_search
functions.desc:
Find cities in a state of your choice.
Example: city_search("California") would return cities in California.

state.description: The name of the state where you're seeking cities.

functions.name: flight_search
functions.desc:
A flight information retrieval tool.
Example: flight_search("New York", "London", "2022-10-01") would fetch flights from New York to London on October 1, 2022.

departure_city.description: The city you'll be flying out from.

destination_city.description: The city you aim to reach.

date.description: The date of your travel in YYYY-MM-DD format.

functions.name: google_distance_matrix
functions.desc:
Estimate the distance, time and cost between two cities.
Example: google_distance_matrix("Paris", "Lyon", "self-driving") would provide driving distance, time and cost between Paris and Lyon.

origin.description: The departure city of your journey.

destination.description: The destination city of your journey.

functions.name: restaurant_search
functions.desc:
Explore dining options in a city of your choice.
Example: restaurant_search("Tokyo") would show a curated list of restaurants in Tokyo.

city.description: The name of the city where you're seeking restaurants.

functions.name: submit_day_plan
functions.desc:
Once you have collected information about the trip, call this function once for each day of the trip, starting on day 1.
If a field does not apply for a given day, use "-" to indicate this.
You MUST call this function to save the plan for each query.

current_city.description: The city for this day. If the plan is to travel between two cities, indicate it as "from A to B" (e.g. "from Ithaca to Charlotte").

transportation.description: e.g. "Flight Number: F3633413, from Ithaca to Charlotte, Departure Time: 05:38, Arrival Time: 07:46"

breakfast.description: The name of a restaurant in the city, e.g. "Nagaland's Kitchen, Charlotte"

attraction.description: Use a ";" to separate different attractions, with each attraction formatted as "Name, City". e.g. "The Charlotte Museum of History, Charlotte;"

accommodation.description: e.g. "Affordable Spacious Refurbished Room in Bushwick!, Charlotte"

## Day 1:
- 11:00: Arrive in Columbus, Ohio via connecting flight.
- 11:30: Check into your accommodation in Columbus, such as the 'Bright room in huge, dog-friendly apt w/ balcony' (93 USD per night) or the 'Huge Private Room in New York 10minute to Midtown' (471 USD per night).
- 13:00: Lunch at the 'Himalya Chinese' restaurant (25 USD per person on average), serving Chinese, American and cafe cuisine.
- 15:00: Visit the Center of Science and Industry (COSI), an interactive science museum with exhibits and activities for all ages.
- 18:00: Enjoy dinner at 'Prem Ji Delhi Wale', a restaurant offering Chinese, American and dessert dishes at an average price of 24 USD per person.

## Day 2:
- 9:00: Breakfast at 'Desire Foods', a French, Mexican and bakery restaurant with an average cost of 23 USD per person.
- 10:30: Explore the Columbus Museum of Art, home to an impressive permanent collection and temporary exhibitions.
- 13:00: Have lunch at 'The Irish House', serving French, Mexican, tea, pizza, dessert, and Mediterranean dishes at an average price of 65 USD per person.
- 14:30: Wander through the Franklin Park Conservatory and Botanical Gardens, a stunning botanical garden and conservatory.
- 18:00: For dinner, try 'Karnataka Food Centre', which serves French, BBQ, cafe, Mediterranean, and fast food at an average cost of 18 USD per person.

## Day 3:
- 7:00: Depart Columbus and take a bus or train to Cleveland.
- 9:30: Arrive in Cleveland and check into your accommodation, like the 'Gorgeous 1-2 BDR apartment in the Lower East Side' (107 USD per night) or 'Pleasant & Low-priced place  in Manhattan' (347 USD per night).
- 11:00: Visit the Cleveland Metroparks Zoo, home to a diverse range of animals and offering various educational programs and events.
- 13:00: Lunch at 'Me Kong Bowl', serving cafe, BBQ, seafood, and dessert cuisine at an average price of 19 USD per person.
- 14:30: Discover the Cleveland Botanical Garden, featuring beautifully landscaped gardens with various plant species and seasonal flower shows.
- 18:00: Dinner at 'Cleveland Harbor West Pierhead Lighthouse', a unique dining experience with a spectacular view, offering various cuisines.

## Day 4:
- 9:00: Breakfast at 'Bikanerwala', serving tea, bakery, BBQ, and fast food at an average cost of 10 USD per person.
- 10:30: Explore the Greater Cleveland Aquarium, known for its diverse marine life and engaging educational programs.
- 12:30: Lunch at 'Makhan Fish and Chicken Corner', offering pizza, French, fast food, Chinese, and seafood at an average price of 25 USD per person.
- 14:00: Visit the Cleveland Museum of Art, renowned for its extensive collection of artworks from various cultures and periods.
- 18:00: Enjoy dinner at 'Five Boroughs', a restaurant serving French, bakery, BBQ, and seafood cuisine at an average cost of 97 USD per person.

## Day 5:
- 10:00: After breakfast, explore the Rock & Roll Hall of Fame, a museum dedicated to the history of rock music.
- 12:00: Lunch at 'Pind Balluchi', serving Chinese, pizza, French, BBQ, and cafe cuisine at an average price of 96 USD per person.
- 13:30: Visit the Cleveland History Center, which showcases the history of Cleveland and Northeast Ohio through various exhibits and artifacts.
- 16:00: Depart from Cleveland to return home.
